Movie: South Park the Streaming Wars Part 2

Review: A small movie I’ve been anticipating since I heard about it. As a fan of Freddie Gibbs’ music and personality, the idea of him starring in a film got me curious and excited. Freddie really has the acting chops and truly shines here. I hope to see him in more acting roles for the future. Also, the confident filmmaking on display really enhances the watch for me, and is appreciated. Sure, it’s a slow burn, and I can nitpick some…

Movie: The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent

Review: A must watch theater experience! Everything about this film needs to be viewed in a theater. This might sound silly, but one of the few films I’ve seen in years, where the audience claps, shouts, and gasps throughout the runtime that wasn’t a comic book movie. Also, I was not expecting to be so emotionally invested in this. I was expecting some great action and filmmaking, but I wasn’t ready for all the emotions that came with this. Bravo to everyone involved. This is why I love cinema.

Movie: Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness
Review: The highs are high, but the lows are low. I can’t be certain, but it felt like my favorite moments were when Sam Raimi had full control, and my least favorite moments were when the studio took control. It seemed at odds with being unique and following the MCU formula checklist.
Blown away by how much I enjoyed this. Never had an interest of watching, but decided to give it a shot, and I’m glad I did. Clean animation, and just a fun watch.

An epic film in every category and a truly cinematic experience. Visually stunning, brutal action, and fantastic performances all around. Robert Eggers has proven to be one of the top craftsman working in cinema.

Basically Grand Theft Auto directed by Michael Bay and it’s beautiful. Highly entertaining and so thrilling. Shouldn’t be over 2 hours long, and if time was shaved off to be under 2 hours this would’ve been damn near perfect as far as entertainment goes.
